HEADWORD: Lockram
<hw>Lock"ram</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>locrenan</ets>, <ets>locronan</ets>; from <ets>Locronan</ets>, in
Brittany, where it is said to have been made.]</ety> <def>A kind of
linen cloth anciently used in England, originally imported from
Brittany.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

